9. Enhanced Input Recommendation

For Enhanced Input, store the actual value inside the input action value, not the InputActionValue wrapper itself.

Recommended mapping:

Boolean input  → bool
Axis1D input   → float
Axis2D input   → Vector2D
Axis3D input   → Vector

Example:

FVector2D MoveValue = Value.Get<FVector2D>();

UDynamicStorageSystemAPI::RegisterData<FVector2D>(
    this,
    FGameplayTag::RequestGameplayTag(TEXT("Input.Action.Move")),
    MoveValue
);


---

10. World Context

The plugin needs a valid world context object.

It works normally inside:

Actor Blueprint
Actor Component Blueprint
Pawn Blueprint
Character Blueprint
Widget Blueprint
Player Controller Blueprint

If using it from a Blueprint that does not have a valid world, pass a valid context object such as:

Actor
Actor Component
Player Controller
Game Instance
Widget
